parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden and unexpected airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
airbag deploys suddenly without any apparent reason
airbag deploys without a crash or accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash
airbag warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
seat belt sensor failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag disable function can lead to unnecessary airbag deployments or failure to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag disable function fails to recognize child seat or passenger
airbag deploys unnecessarily
front passenger airbag does not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift lock can cause the vehicle to shift gears unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control. Additionally, it can also cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear, making it difficult or impossible to drive.
symptoms: The shift gear moves freely from park to drive while the vehicle is off
the vehicle can be shifted into gear without pressing the brake
the vehicle will not move after being parked
the vehicle will not start after being turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Deceleration and Check Engine Light Illumination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent deceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, potentially leading to accidents. The illumination of the check engine light can indicate a serious problem with the engine, which if left unchecked, can lead to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The vehicle decelerates instead of accelerating when pressing the accelerator
the check engine warning light illuminates intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension spring mounting can cause the suspension spring to fall out, leading to a loss of vehicle control, potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The suspension spring falls out
the vehicle's ride height changes
the vehicle becomes unstable
unusual noises or vibrations are felt while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the jack can cause it to fall over, potentially leading to injuries or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The jack falls over on its own while in use
instability of the jack during tire changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause incorrect or scrambled information to be displayed, potentially leading to confusion or distraction while driving.
symptoms: Scrambled time display
incorrect outside temperature display
repeated failure of the instrument cluster despite replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the cup holder on the 2000 E430 Mercedes Benz, which is located over the shifting mechanism, can cause the electrical system to shut down if a liquid is spilled, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks and slows down
the electrical system shuts down
the gear shift mechanism is exposed and vulnerable to liquid spills.
